# Internationalization (i18n)

## Language Priority
- Primary: Bahasa Indonesia (id)
- Secondary: English (en)
- All user-facing strings MUST exist in both languages
- Clinical terms: use Indonesian common name + English medical term in parentheses
  Example: "Tekanan Darah (Blood Pressure)"

## Chrome Extension i18n
- Use `chrome.i18n.getMessage()` for manifest strings
- Store translations in `public/_locales/{lang}/messages.json`
- Default locale in manifest.json: `"default_locale": "id"`

## React i18n
- Use a lightweight i18n library (e.g., `react-i18next` or custom hook)
- Never hardcode user-facing text in JSX — always use translation keys
- Translation keys: `camelCase` with component prefix: `sidepanel.dashboard.title`

## Clinical Terminology
- Medical terms MUST follow Indonesian Ministry of Health (Kemenkes) standard terminology
- Drug names: use generic names, not brand names
- ICD-10 codes: display code + Indonesian description
- Forbidden: machine-translating clinical terms without physician review
